  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle, then preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ 425°F/ Gas 7</p>\n<p>Cut the<strong> potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-<span class=\"text-highlight\">sized</span> pieces</p>\n<p>Add the<strong> potatoes</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 10-15 min or until fork-tender</p>\n<p>Once cooked, drain and leave to steam dry</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/880.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/880.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/880.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/880.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/880.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, separate the <strong>spring greens</strong> leaves, discarding any tough stalks</p>\n<p>Layer the leaves over each other, roll them up and slice into thin strips</p>\n<p>Trim and finely chop the<strong> spring onions </strong></p>\n<p>Cut the <strong>red </strong><span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>onions</strong></span> into wedges, leaving the skins and root on (this stops them drying out and falling apart when roasting)</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/880.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/880.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/880.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/880.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/880.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Reboil a kettle</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>cumberland sausages</strong> and <strong>onion wedges</strong> to a baking tray (use <strong>tin foil</strong> to avoid mess!)</p>\n<p>Drizzle the <strong>onion wedges</strong> with <strong>olive oil</strong> and season with <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong></p>\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until the sausages are cooked through and the onion wedges have softened</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/880.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/880.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/880.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/880.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/880.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the<strong> spring greens</strong> and <strong>spring onion</strong> and cook for 2 min</p>\n<p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and add a splash of<strong> water</strong></p>\n<p>Cook, covered, for 2-3 min or until softened, then transfer to a plate and set aside (reserve the pan for later!)</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/880.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/880.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/880.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/880.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/880.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, dissolve the <strong>beef stock cube<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in 300ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [600ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> with the <strong>redcurrant jelly</strong> <span class=\"text-highlight\">–</span> this is your <strong>redcurrant stock</strong></p>\n<p>Wipe the reserved pan clean and return it to a medium heat</p>\n<p>Once hot, add a knob of<strong> butter</strong></p>\n<p>Once melted, add 1/2 tsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [1 tsp]</span><strong> flour</strong> and cook for 1 min, stirring with a wooden spoon until combined</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/880.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/880.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/880.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/880.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/880.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>Chinese rice</strong><strong> wine</strong> and cook for 20 sec or until dissolved, then add the <strong>redcurrant stock</strong> and whisk until combined</p>\n<p>Cook for 6-8 min or until thickened to a sticky gravy-like consistency, whisking occasionally <span class=\"text-highlight\">–</span> this is your <strong>redcurrant jelly gravy</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/880.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/880.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/880.-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/880.-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/880.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the<strong> potatoes</strong> to their pot with a large knob of <strong>butter</strong> and a splash of<strong> milk</strong></p>\n<p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong> and mash until smooth</p>\n<p>Stir through the <strong>spring greens</strong> <span class=\"text-highlight\">–</span> this is your<strong> colcannon</strong></p>\n<p>Once cooked, remove the <strong>sausages</strong> from the oven</p>\n<p>Remove the skins and roots from the onion so that you are left with separated onion pieces <span class=\"text-highlight\">–</span> these are your <strong>onion petals </strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/880.-step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/880.-step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/880.-step-7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/880.-step-7-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/880.-step-7-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>sausages</strong> on top of the <strong>colcannon</strong> with the<strong> onion petals</strong> around the plate</p>\n<p>Drizzle with<strong> redcurrant jelly gravy</strong></p>\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
